title: For Sale/Trade:  Hunter Arms Fulton 12ga Side by Side - NICE!
postcontent: An excellent example of a ‘Fulton” double barrel shotgun as manufactured by Hunter Arms. Serial number is in the 20x,xxx range and I believe the gun was made soon after the end of World War Two, circa 1945. All matching numbers, 30 inch barrels, 12 gage, with excellent bores. Not marked for choke but supposedly made in modified(R) and full (L). Very tight action has apparently seen little use. Case-hardened finish on the receiver, etc. is just fading the slightest and looks near new. Barrel finish is completely blue going to plum in just a few areas but worn only slightly at the muzzles and breech. Barrels and rib are solid. Wood has nice hand cut checkering with the slightest of handling marks. A vintage Pachmayr ‘White Line” recoil pad is fitted, most likely when the gun was purchased new. A really nice clean example of the Working Man’s L.C. Smith; among the nicest of the type I've seen. Asking $450. I don't do text. E-mail only please.

title: For Sale:  FEG PA-63 Pistol With Wolf Springs
postcontent:
The FEG PA-63 pistol was developed during early 1960s at the Hungarian FEG arms factory as a compact military sidearm, chambered for the Warsaw pact standard 9x18 Makarov ammunition of Soviet origin. The basic design of the FEG PA-63 pistol was heavily based on the German Walther PP pistol, a copy of which was produced by FEG shortly after the WW2. 
The FEG PA-63 pistol is a simple blowback operated weapon. The return spring is located around the barrel, the trigger is of traditional double-action type with exposed hammer. Manual safety lever, which doubles as a decocker, is located at the left side of the slide. Gun is fed from single stack box magazines, magazine release button is located on the left side of the frame, above and behind the trigger.
Comes with 1 magazine, box, papers, Wolf  9Lb. and 13 Lb. reduced power hammer springs (9Lb. hammer spring installed) Wolf recoil spring and original factory springs.
Buyer pays FFL fee of $20.00  NH Sales Only
